1. How to start the jenkins container from image 

$ docker run -t -p local_port:container_port --name=<name_of_container> -d <docker_image>
$ docker run -t -p 8080:8080 --name=jenkins -d foxylion/jenkins

2. How to check what containers are running 

$ docker ps -a

3. How to login to a container as a root 

$ docker exec -i -t --user=root <container_name> /bin/bash

4. How to run a command in container 

$ docker exec -i -t <container_name> <command>

5. How to restart a container 

$ docker restart <container name or ID>

6. How to stop a container 

$ docker stop <container_name>

7. How to start a container 

$ docker start <container_name>

8. How remove a container 

$ docker rm <container_name>

9. How to pull an image to docker 

$ docker pull <image_name>

10. How to delete a image in docker 

$ docker rmi <image_name>

11. How to attach to an running container 

$ docker attach <container_name> 

Note : This is almost like a console and you will be able to see output on tty if it started via "-t" option and to detech you need to use "ctrl - c" or "ctrl -p " or "ctrl -q"

